FAQs
What are the benefits of studying at Tbilisi State Medical University?
TSMU offers high-quality education, affordable tuition fees, English-taught programs, excellent clinical training, modern facilities, and a diverse, inclusive environment.

How can Qadri-International help me study at TSMU?
Qadri-International provides comprehensive guidance, application assistance, visa support, financial planning, and pre-departure and post-arrival support to ensure a smooth study abroad experience.

Are there English-taught medical programs at TSMU?
Yes, TSMU offers medical programs taught in English, making it accessible for international students.

What are the costs associated with studying at TSMU?
Tuition fees range from $4,000 to $8,000 per year, and living expenses average between $300 and $600 per month. Scholarships and financial aid are available to help reduce these costs.
